    <remarks variants="9">
        <remark source-urls="1">
            <p>Foreign Service Officer. Permanent Representative of the U.S.A. to the Organization of American States (Washington); Ambassador Extraordinary and Plenipotentiary (Mexico); Ambassador Extraordinary and Plenipotentiary (Honduras).</p>
            <source-url>https://history.state.gov/departmenthistory/people/jova-joseph-john</source-url>
        </remark>
        <remark source-urls="1">
            <p>Consul of the Embassy in Portugal until February 1957; Officer in Charge of French-Iberian Affairs, Bureau of European Affairs, Department of State, from March 1957</p>
            <source-url>https://history.state.gov/historicaldocuments/frus1955-57v27/persons#p_JJJ1</source-url>
        </remark>
        <remark source-urls="1">
            <p>Officer in Charge of French-Iberian Affairs, Department of State, until September 1958</p>
            <source-url>https://history.state.gov/historicaldocuments/frus1958-60v13/persons#p_JJJ1</source-url>
        </remark>
        <remark source-urls="1">
            <p>Deputy Chief of Mission in Chile until May 1965; Ambassador to Honduras from June 7, 1965</p>
            <source-url>https://history.state.gov/historicaldocuments/frus1964-68v31/persons#p_JJJ1</source-url>
        </remark>
        <remark source-urls="1">
            <p>U.S.Permanent Representative to the Organization of American States, also U.S. Representative to the OAS Council from July 1969</p>
            <source-url>https://history.state.gov/historicaldocuments/frus1969-76ve01/persons#p_JJJ1</source-url>
        </remark>
        <remark source-urls="1">
            <p>United States Ambassador to United Mexican States from January 1974</p>
            <source-url>https://history.state.gov/historicaldocuments/frus1969-76ve03/persons#p_JJJ1</source-url>
        </remark>
        <remark source-urls="1">
            <p>U.S. Ambassador to Honduras from January 1969 until June 1969; U.S. representative on the Council of the Organization of American States with rank of Ambassador from June 1969 until February 1970; Chief of Mission-Overall U.S. Representative to the Organization of American States from February 1970; Permanent Representative to the Organization of American States with rank of Ambassador from May 1971</p>
            <source-url>https://history.state.gov/historicaldocuments/frus1969-76ve10/persons#p_JJJ1</source-url>
        </remark>
        <remark source-urls="1">
            <p>Permanent Representative of the United States to the Organization of American States from July 8, 1969, until January 13, 1974; U.S. Ambassador to Mexico from January 30, 1974, until February 21, 1977</p>
            <source-url>https://history.state.gov/historicaldocuments/frus1969-76ve11p1/persons#p_JJJ_1</source-url>
        </remark>
        <remark source-urls="1">
            <p>U.S. Ambassador to Mexico from January 1974</p>
            <source-url>https://history.state.gov/historicaldocuments/frus1969-76ve14p1/persons#p_JJJ1</source-url>
        </remark>
